The hotel is new and the rooms are reasonably nice and brand new, but not really up to Four Seasons standards.	The Four Seasons Seattle is brand spanking new and was the reason we chose to drive down from Vancouver for a few days over the holidays.	On the plus side the rooms are nicely furnished, the pool (and gym) have great views, food was excellent in the restaurant and service up to normal Four Seasons standards.	The hotel is fairly new and definitely up to 4 seasons standards, similar to the one in Denver in decor.	for a hotel group with the reputation of the four seasons the service level is not what i expected.